About Forensic and Litigation Consulting:

The Forensic & Litigation Consulting practice offers one of the industry's most complete range of advisory services to clients across the world. Our service offerings include anti-money laundering compliance and investigations; Bribery and corruption investigations; forensic accounting; fraud and other financial crime investigations; governance, risk and regulatory advice; regulatory investigations and litigation support and transactional data analytics.

ABOUT THE OPPORTUNITY:

FTI Consulting's Construction Solutions business unit is seeking ambitious and hard-working professionals with experience in construction claims and disputes to join its forensic delay experts in Paris.

As part of the Forensic and Litigation Consulting practice, our Construction Solutions group offers a broad range of contract advisory services to assist owners/employers, contractors and construction law firms in the prevention, mitigation or resolution of construction disputes.

The successful individual will have a qualification in engineering or construction management with experience in managing the delivery of construction contracts. The level of construction claims experience and forensic delay analysis, together with any additional qualifications in law/construction law will dictate the entry level of the candidate.

FTI Consulting can offer a competitive and attractive rewards package, training and development opportunities, a supportive and friendly environment and the opportunity to achieve the individual's full potential.


PRIMARY DUTIES - CONSULTANT:
Grasp the issues facing our clients and understand the importance of our service offerings;
Analysis of construction programmes and other project records;
Assist with the preparation of claim/expert reports;
Provide a timely and high-quality service to clients that is proportionate to our client's issues and budget constraints; and
Comply with the Quality Assurance procedures of the practice.




BASIC QUALIFICATIONS:

Bachelor's degree or degree equivalent in Engineering or Construction Management;
Secondary qualifications in Construction Law or Arbitration are a plus;
Member of a professional body such as ICE or CIOB.

PREFERRED SKILLS:

Proficient in Microsoft Office package; e.g. Word, Excel, and PowerPoint;
Experience in planning software; e.g. Microsoft Project, Asta Powerproject and Primavera P6;
Ability to manage multiple tasks and prioritise changing workloads;
Ability to work independently, exercise good judgment and resourcefulness;
Ability to work well under pressure;
Professional, confident demeanour and appearance;
Experience and willingness in business development activities;
Proactive individual with strong drive, ambition and enthusiasm;
Excellent communication and presentation skills (oral and written);
Capable of supporting positions with rational arguments;
Team player with positive and energetic attitude.


